    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is Pinia?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Pinia is the official state management library for Vue, designed to replace Vuex with a simpler and more modern API."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use Pinia?"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Simple and intuitive API**",
        "**Better TypeScript support**",
        "**Lightweight and fast**",
        "**DevTools integration**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Install Pinia"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "bash",
      "value": "npm install pinia"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Setup Pinia"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "import { createApp } from 'vue';\nimport { createPinia } from 'pinia';\n\nconst app = createApp(App);\napp.use(createPinia());\napp.mount('#app');"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Create Store"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "import { defineStore } from 'pinia';\n\nexport const useStore = defineStore('main', {\n  state: () => ({ count: 0 }),\n  actions: {\n    increment() {\n      this.count++;\n    }\n  },\n  getters: {\n    doubleCount: (state) => state.count * 2\n  }\n});"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Store"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const store = useStore();\nstore.increment();\nconsole.log(store.count);"
    },
